Dodge skills in the context of JABS all do the same
general thing:\. move the player forcefully in a direction,\.
usually at a higher speed than normal.
The direction decided is based on the notes,\. either
Forward and backward are relative to the direction you're
currently facing and would send you in the respective direction
"Directional" however can send the player in any direction!\.
It will default to "forward" if you're not pressing a direction,\.
but if you're holding a direction,\. it'll go that way instead.
In combination with the type of movement the dodge skill
will perform\. you the RM dev can also decide how far to go in
the given direction,\. and also whether or not the player
is invincible for the duration of the movement.
And if you feel like it,\. they can have cooldowns like
regular action skills (or no cooldown),\. and can have costs
like regular action skills (or be free).
In the case of right here and now,\. \C[1]Tumble\C[0] is
free, "directional", and moves 3 spaces.\.\. It should be
just enough to get you safely through this hot mess of
fireball traps I laid out before you.
